This paper discusses natural language processing (NLP) models and their evaluation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of modeling tools and algorithms, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of adversarial roles and the use of error analysis could also be relevant to computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.CC).
